# Parachute Commons License (PCL) 2.0

**🪂 A license that deploys protection as the stakes get closer to the ground.**

*Version 2.0 | 2026*
*A fair-code license for shared work in a volatile information era.*

---

## 0. Plain-language summary (not the license)

This summary is for orientation only and has no legal force. The operative
terms are Sections 1–11.

A parachute stays packed until it's needed. This license starts fully
permissive — you can read, share, adapt, and build on the Work for free. As use
gets closer to large-scale extraction, the protections deploy: significant
commercial or institutional use requires acknowledgment and fair contribution
back, and a narrow set of abusive uses are prohibited outright.

This is a source-available, fair-code license.

---

## 1. Definitions

**1.1 "Work"** means the material licensed under this License, including text,
documentation, methodologies, frameworks, templates, designs, data, and source
code, together with any portion of it.

**1.2 "Licensor"** means the individual or entity that holds rights in the Work
and offers it under this License. The Licensor is identified in the Work's
`LICENSE` file or accompanying notice.

**1.3 "You"** means any individual or entity exercising rights under this
License.

**1.4 "Derivative"** means any work that adapts, translates, remixes, extends,
or is based upon the Work, in any medium.

**1.5 "Distribute"** means to make the Work or a Derivative available to any
third party, by any means, including hosting, transmission, or incorporation
into a product or service.

**1.6 "Commercial Use"** means use of the Work or a Derivative primarily
intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.
Use is **not** Commercial Use solely because it occurs within a for-profit
entity; internal evaluation, research, and individual professional use below
the Threshold remain permissive under Section 2.

**1.7 "Threshold Entity"** means a User that, together with its affiliates,
meets or exceeds **any** of the following in the most recent twelve (12)
months:
  (a) **USD $1,000,000** in total gross revenue; **or**
  (b) **USD $1,000,000** in total outside capital raised; **or**
  (c) **50** or more full-time-equivalent personnel.

A User below all three is a **"Permissive User"** and is governed only by
Section 2, regardless of for-profit status.

**1.8 "Automated Ingestion at Scale"** means incorporating the Work or a
Derivative into a training corpus, model, index, or other automated system in a
manner that reproduces, abstracts, or redistributes the Work's substance
without preserving the attribution required by Section 3.

**1.9 "Provenance"** means the identification of the Licensor as the originating
human creator of the Work, and the relationship of any Derivative to the Work.

---

## 2. Phase One — Permissive Grant (the packed parachute)

Subject to Section 4, the Licensor grants You a worldwide, royalty-free,
non-exclusive license to:

  (a) read, run, study, and share the Work;
  (b) create and Distribute Derivatives; and
  (c) use the Work and Derivatives for personal, educational, research,
      internal-evaluation, and individual professional purposes.

**You must, in all cases:**

  (i) preserve Provenance — credit the Licensor as the original human
      creator, and link to the source Work where reasonably possible;
  (ii) state, in any Derivative, that it is derived from the Work and how;
  (iii) preserve this License text and notice with any copy or Derivative.

Phase One applies fully and indefinitely to every **Permissive User**. Nothing
in later phases restricts a Permissive User acting within this Section.

---

## 3. Phase Two — Deployed Protections (commercial and institutional scale)

When a use is **both** (x) Commercial Use **or** institutional deployment, and
(y) carried out by a **Threshold Entity**, the following additional terms apply.
They supplement, and do not remove, the obligations in Section 2.

**3.1 Acknowledgment.** Threshold Entities must include a visible attribution in
the relevant product, documentation, or interface:
"Includes work protected under the Parachute Commons License — © [Licensor]."

**3.2 Fair Contribution.** Threshold Entities making Commercial Use must, before
or promptly upon crossing into Commercial Use, contact the Licensor and agree in
good faith to **one** of:
  (a) a reasonable commercial license fee; or
  (b) another agreed contribution that sustains the Work (funding, materially
      significant upstream contribution, or shared value to the originating
      community).
The default expectation, absent other agreement, is a reasonable,
proportionate fee negotiated in good faith. The Licensor will not unreasonably
withhold permission where fair contribution is offered.

**3.3 Derivative Transparency.** A Threshold Entity Distributing a Derivative
must clearly state the Derivative's relationship to the Work and must not
present the Derivative in a way that conceals the Work's origin.

**3.4 Automated Ingestion.** Automated Ingestion at Scale by a Threshold Entity
requires the Licensor's prior written permission. Ingestion that preserves
Provenance and does not redistribute the Work's substance does not by itself
require permission.

**3.5 Grace Period.** A User that crosses the Threshold while already using the
Work has **ninety (90) days** to come into compliance with Section 3 from the
date it becomes a Threshold Entity.

---

## 4. Phase Three — Prohibited Uses (egregious misuse)

The following uses are prohibited for **all** Users regardless of scale, and no
grant in Sections 2 or 3 extends to them:

  (a) **Impersonation** — using the Work or a Derivative to falsely represent
      the Licensor as the author of, or endorser of, material the Licensor did
      not create or endorse;
  (b) **Falsification of intent** — using the Work in a manner that materially
      distorts or inverts its evident purpose in order to mislead;
  (c) **Provenance laundering** — removing, obscuring, or falsifying Provenance
      to appropriate the Work as one's own or another's;
  (d) **Unlawful harm** — using the Work to facilitate activity that is
      unlawful or that causes foreseeable serious harm to others.

---

## 5. Termination and Reinstatement

**5.1** Rights under this License terminate automatically upon a material breach
You do not cure within **thirty (30) days** of becoming aware of it, or
immediately upon any violation of Section 4.

**5.2** Rights reinstate automatically upon cure of a Section 2 or 3 breach,
unless the Licensor has, before cure, notified You that the License is finally
terminated for that breach. Section 4 violations do not auto-reinstate; they
require the Licensor's written reinstatement.

**5.3** Termination does not affect the rights of Permissive Users or downstream
recipients who remain in compliance.

---

## 6. Patent and Moral Rights

**6.1** Each Licensor who contributes code or technical method to the Work
grants You a non-exclusive, royalty-free patent license to that contribution, to
the extent necessary to exercise the rights granted herein. This patent grant
terminates for any party that initiates patent litigation alleging the Work
infringes a patent.

**6.2** Where moral rights of attribution and integrity exist by law, the
Licensor retains them; the Provenance obligations in this License are intended
to honor, not waive, those rights.

---

## 7. Trademarks

This License grants no rights in the Licensor's names, logos, or trademarks,
except the limited use required to satisfy the attribution and acknowledgment
obligations in Sections 2 and 3.

---

## 8. Enforcement and Culture

This License is enforceable as a copyright license. It is **also** maintained,
by design, through community norms: voluntary disclosure by responsible
reusers, active care by Licensors, and a shared culture of honoring Provenance.
The Licensor may pursue available legal remedies for breach, or may resolve
breaches through community-led correction where that better serves the Work.
Choosing the latter in one instance does not waive the former in another.

