## 10. Limitation of Liability

TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, THE LICENSOR WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY
INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR EXEMPLARY DAMAGES ARISING FROM
THE WORK OR ITS USE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.

## 11. Severability and Versioning

**11.1** If any provision is held unenforceable, the remainder stays in effect,
and the unenforceable provision applies to the maximum extent permitted.

**11.2** The Licensor may publish revised versions of this License. The Work is
governed by the version stated in its notice; absent a stated version, You may
use the Work under any version the Licensor has published.

**11.3** Where compliance with any term is impossible due to statute, judicial
order, or regulation, You must comply to the maximum extent possible and
describe the limitation in a notice distributed with the Work.

---

## How to apply this License

1. Add a `LICENSE` file containing this full text to your project.

2. Add this notice to the Work and to key files:

   ```
   This Work is licensed under the Parachute Commons License 2.0.
   © [year] [Licensor]. Source: [link]
   🪂 Shared for inquiry and contribution; protected from extractive use.
   If a copy of the PCL was not distributed with this file, see
   https://github.com/quarterback/parachute-commons-license.
   ```

3. Set your Threshold values in Section 1.7 if you wish to depart from the
   defaults, and state any departure clearly in your notice.

